                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.00/753: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Muccio</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-05-17T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 17, 1936—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:53 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>22. My telegram May 17, noon. Manifesto by Acting Chief of General Staff declares
                    that after consulting army, Republican Socialists and Socialists Parties mixed
                    Junta assumes charge of the Government at 5:30 today. Junta consisting of four
                    military, two Republican Socialists and two Socialists with Colonel Toro as
                    President of Junta. La Paz continues tranquil.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Muccio</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
